OL,3,CEducation Minister ignored official
OL,4,Cadvice when he agreed to meet the LCC
OL,6,FThere was particular criticism of the
OL,7,FEducation Minister when it was
OL,8,Fconfirmed the LCC had raised its
OL,9,Fobjections to an Irish language school
OL,10,Fin east Belfast.
OL,12,FOther community organisations also
OL,13,Fexpressed frustrations that they had
OL,14,Fbeen seeking meetings with both DUP
OL,15,Fministers which have not been granted.
OL,17,FBoth the LCC and the ministers said
OL,18,Fthe meetings were to discuss
OL,19,Feducational underachievement in
OL,20,Floyalist areas, as well as social and
OL,21,Feconomic deprivation in communities.
