OL,3,CEducation Minister ignored official
OL,4,Cadvice when he agreed to meet the LCC
OL,6,FThe 'Quick Advice' recommendation that
OL,7,Fthe minister should not hold the
OL,8,Fmeeting was sent to his special
OL,9,Fadvisor on the 6th March.
OL,11,FOfficials also drew up two versions of
OL,12,Fa letter of response for the minister
OL,13,Fto sign. One agreeing to the meeting,
OL,14,Fand one declining citing 'diary
OL,15,Fpressures' as the reason the meeting
OL,16,Fcould not take place.
OL,18,FPaul Givan signed the letter accepting
OL,19,Fthe invitation to meet on the 17th
OL,20,FMay. Eleven weeks after the request
OL,21,Fwas first made.
